  {
    "client_msg_id": "f26b590c-882b-4559-9c91-a56302fa2feb",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Yes, that's true. I'm a big fan of FORTH, having used it a lot in the 80's and am even writing a lexically-scoped OO FORTH-like system: <https://github.com/kgrgreer/TURTLES/tree/main> .  Also, some early microcomputers (<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MCM/70>) used APL, but neither APL nor FORTH were as accessible as BASIC. LOGO, which is a simplified dialect of LISP, and actually a pretty good language, might have been a better choice. But people looked down on it because of its use with Turtle graphics and being for kids, but it is actually a much better language than BASIC (or just about anything else at the time).",
    "user": "U01U19ECZTJ",
    "ts": "1686660302.809199",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "Mgtv/",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Yes, that's true. I'm a big fan of FORTH, having used it a lot in the 80's and am even writing a lexically-scoped OO FORTH-like system: "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://github.com/kgrgreer/TURTLES/tree/main"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " .  Also, some early microcomputers ("
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MCM/70"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ") used APL, but neither APL nor FORTH were as accessible as BASIC. LOGO, which is a simplified dialect of LISP, and actually a pretty good language, might have been a better choice. But people looked down on it because of its use with Turtle graphics and being for kids, but it is actually a much better language than BASIC (or just about anything else at the time)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
