    "client_msg_id": "6209055a-f212-426f-8c7c-31f05f93b803",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "That's an interesting observation for me because (1) it's clearly true, (2) looks like a good characteristic for newbies but (3) is also exactly why I didn't like BASIC. I wanted to get details out of my view, to focus on a bigger picture. My solution was printing the code, with subroutines on separate pages, starting with a comment that gave a name to the subroutine. Each `gosub` also had a comment with the name of the subroutine being called.",
